et to \\\"Delete\\\") within the control is clicked, but before the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.FormView> control deletes the record. This allows you to provide an event-handling method that performs a custom routine, such as verifying a record before deleting it, whenever this event occurs.  \\n  \\n When you create a FormViewDeleteEventHandler delegate, you identify the method that will handle the event. To associate the event with your event handler, add an instance of the delegate to the event. The event handler is called whenever the event occurs, unless you remove the delegate. For more information about event-handler delegates, see [NIB: Events and Delegates](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/d98fd58b-fa4f-4598-8378-addf4355a115).\"\n  example:\n  - \"The following example demonstrates how to programmatically add a FormViewDeleteEventHandler delegate to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.FormView.ItemDeleting> event of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.FormView> control.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[FormViewDeleteEventHandler2#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_188_1.aspx)]\\n [!code-vb[FormViewDeleteEventHandler2#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_188_1.aspx)]  \\n  \\n The following example demonstrates how to declaratively add a FormViewDeleteEventHandler delegate to the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.FormView.ItemDeleting> event of a <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.FormView> control.  \\n  \\n [!code-cs[FormViewDeleteEventHandlerDeclarative2#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_188_2.aspx)]\\n [!code-vb[FormViewDeleteEventHandlerDeclarative2#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/t-system.web.ui.webcontr_188_2.aspx)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public delegate void FormViewDeleteEventHandler(object sender, FormViewDeleteEventArgs e);\n  inheritance:\n  - System.Delegate\n  platform:\n  - net462\nreferences:\n- uid: System.Delegate\n  isExternal: false\n  name: System.Delegate\n"}